This paper deals with sentiment analysis of tweets, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as K-means clustering, Decision Trees, and Support Vector Machines, which are commonly used in data mining and machine learning. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques such as text mining and classification, which could place it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with social media, which could place it under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
